cs.RO, cs.AI, cs.CV, cs.NE, cs.LG. 

This paper presents a humanoid robot interacting with the world using a perception and control algorithm based on the free-energy principle. The paper focuses on the challenges of interacting under uncertainty and the advantages of using active inference for real-world applications. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.RO (Robotics and Control). The paper also discusses the use of human brain-like inspired perception and control algorithms, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper involves object tracking in the visual field, which could fall under cs.CV (Computer Vision). The use of the free-energy principle and the discussion of unconscious processes suggest that it could also belong to cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the paper discusses the advantages of the algorithm for real-world applications, which could fall under cs.LG (Machine Learning).
